snippet: Tens of thousands of opposition supporters converged on the capital in an attempt to force Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif to resign after just 14 months in office.
abstract: Tens of thousands of opposition supporters converge on Islamabad, Pakistan, as part of extended protest movement to oust Prime Min Nawaz Sharif; protests are led by former cricket star Imran Khan, and cleric Muhammad Tahir-ul Qadri.

byline.original: By SALMAN MASOOD and DECLAN WALSH
byline.contributor: Salman Masood reported from Islamabad, and Declan Walsh from London. Ihsanullah Tipu Mehsud contributed reporting from Islamabad.

lead_paragraph: Tens of thousands of opposition supporters converged on the capital in an attempt to force Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif to resign after just 14 months in office.

headline.main: Opposition in Pakistan Is Drenched but Not Doused
headline.print_headline: Opposition in Pakistan Is Drenched but Not Doused
